Ton van den Brink, Associate Professor, University of Utrecht
The &lsquo;Five Presidents&rsquo; Report&rsquo; proposes significant changes to the EU&rsquo;s Economic and Monetary Union (EMU), aiming to deepen its integration. These proposals have substantial implications for national parliaments. A more democratic EMU requires giving these parliaments more authority, going beyond the suggested increased &ldquo;dialogues.&rdquo;
The report advocates for a &ldquo;system of further sovereignty sharing within common institutions,&rdquo; impacting national parliaments by centralizing economic policy coordination within the EU.
